{{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = |name = Hardo Aasmäe |honorific-suffix = |image = Aasmäe.IMG 3094.JPG |imagesize = |smallimage = <!--If this is specified, "image" should not be.--> |alt = |caption = Hardo Aasmäe in 2010 |order = |office = [[Mayor of Tallinn]] |term_start = 1990 |term_end = 1992 |predecessor = [[Harri Lumi]] |successor = [[Jaak Tamm]] |majority = |birth_date = {{birth date|1951|2|11|df=y}} |birth_place = Rannamõisa, [[Martna Parish]], [[Lääne County]], [[Estonia]] |death_date = {{death date and age|2014|12|29|1951|2|11|df=y}} |death_place = [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]] |nationality = Estonian |party = [[Estonian People's Front]] |spouse = |partner = <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married--> |relations = |children = |residence = |alma_mater = [[University of Tartu]], [[Saint Petersburg State University|Leningrad State University]] |occupation = |profession = [[Radio Producer]], [[Geographer]] }}
'''Hardo Aasmäe''' (11 February 1951 – 2 December 2014) was an Estonian [[geography|geographer]], [[business|entrepreneur]] and [[politics|politician]].
He was active in the [[Estonian People's Front]], and was the first post-[[Soviet Union|Soviet]] mayor of [[Tallinn]], from 1990 to 1992.<ref>[http://www.ohtuleht.ee/index.aspx?id=347532 www.ohtuleht.ee]{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.delfi.ee/news/paevauudised/eesti/suri-poliitik-ja-uhiskonnategelane-hardo-aasmae?id=70458457|title=Suri poliitik ja ühiskonnategelane Hardo Aasmäe|publisher=delfi.ee|date=December 30, 2014|language=Estonian}}</ref>
He was for many years the editor-in-chief of the [[Estonian Encyclopaedia]].
Aasmäe produced many radio shows and was a member of ''Tarkade klubi'', an Estonian question-and-answer radio programme, for many years.
He was a member of [[Club of Rome]] Estonian section.
