{{Infobox person | name = Jean Guerrero | image = | residence = California, USA | occupation = Investigative Journalist | website = https://jeanguerrero.com/ }}
'''Jean Guerrero''' (born 1988)<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/entertainment/books/sd-me-festival-guerrero-20180720-story.html|title=Young writer chases her father's past in cross-border memoir|last=Wilkens|first=John|work=sandiegouniontribune.com|access-date=2018-08-24|language=en-US}}</ref> is an investigative journalist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/will-trumps-wall-ever-be-built|title=Will Trump’s wall ever be built?|website=PBS NewsHour|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2016/03/29/472309572/why-tijuanas-tunnel-people-take-the-risk|title=Why Tijuana's 'Tunnel People' Take The Risk|work=NPR.org|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en}}</ref> and a former foreign correspondent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sdcitybeat.com/special-issues/best-of-san-diego-people/best-of-san-diego-2017-people-jean-guerrero/|title=Best of San Diego 2017: People {{!}} Jean Guerrero|last=Combs|first=Seth|date=2017-11-15|work=San Diego CityBeat|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en-us}}</ref> She is the author of the memoir: ''Crux: A Cross-Border Memoir,'' (2018, [[Oneworld Publications|One World]]: [[Random House]])<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bitchmedia.org/article/crux-Jean-Guerrero/memoir-father-family-memory|title=Jean Guerrero’s "Crux" Puts a Reporter’s Lens on Family, Memory, and Culture|work=Bitch Media|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en}}</ref> which won the PEN/FUSION Emerging Writers Award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kpbs.org/news/2018/jul/17/kpbs-journalist-jean-guerrero-traces-family-histor/|title=KPBS Journalist Jean Guerrero Traces Family History In New Memoir 'Crux'|last=Cavanaugh|first=Marissa Cabrera, Maureen|work=KPBS Public Media|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en}}</ref><ref name="PEN America">{{Cite news|url=https://pen.org/press-release/san-diego-reporter-jean-guerrero-takes-10000-penfusion-prize-for-crux/|title=San Diego reporter Jean Guerrero takes $10,000 PEN/FUSION Prize for "Crux" - PEN America|work=PEN America|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en-US}}</ref> Her [[KPBS (TV)|KPBS]] series ''America’s Wall''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kpbs.org/news/2017/nov/13/americas-wall/|title=America's Wall|last=Castañeda|first=Jean Guerrero, Leo|work=KPBS Public Media|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en}}</ref> has won two [[Emmy Award|emmys]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://nataspsw.org/emmy-nominations-2018/|title=Emmy Nominations 2018 - NATAS PSW|date=2018-05-03|work=NATAS PSW|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en-US}}</ref> Guerrero is the Vice President of the [[National Association of Hispanic Journalists]] for San Diego and Tijuana.
== Education == Guerrero received her B.A. in Journalism from [[University of Southern California]]<ref name="prhspeakers.com">{{Cite web|url=https://www.prhspeakers.com/speaker/jean-guerrero|title=Jean Guerrero - Penguin Random House Speakers Bureau|website=www.prhspeakers.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref> and her MFA in creative nonfiction from [[Goucher College]].<ref name="prhspeakers.com"/>
