== ''Crux: A Cross-Border Memoir'' == ''Crux: A Cross-Border Memoir'' was published in 2018 by One World: Random House. The book is an exploration of borders, Guerrero's father, and eventually Guerrero's own sense of self.<ref name=":0" /> Guerrero has commented on the foreign affair issues that exist between the United States and Mexico, and the identities of Mexican-Americans living within this contested cultural climate. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thirteen.org/openmind/civil-rights/immigration-dignity-and-u-s-mexico-relations/6044/|title=Immigration, Dignity, and U.S.-Mexico Relations |last=Hefner |first=Alexander |last2=Guerrero |first2=Jean |date=October 16, 2018 |website= The Open Mind, Thirteen |access-date=October 28, 2018}}</ref>
