{{no footnotes|date=September 2014}} '''''Parroquia''''' ({{IPA-es|paˈrokja|lang}}, {{IPA-gl|paˈrɔkia|lang}}, [[grammatical number|pl.]] ''parroquias''; {{IPA-all|paˈrokia|Asturian:}}, [[grammatical number|pl.]] ''parroquies'') or '''''Parròquia''''' ({{IPA-ca|pəˈrɔkiə|lang}} [[grammatical number|pl.]] ''parròquies'') is a term equivalent to the English [[Parish (country subdivision)|Parish]]; used in [[Andorra]], [[Ecuador]], [[Venezuela]], [[Peru]] and some parts of northwestern [[Spain]].
It can be found in the following countries: *[[Parròquia (Andorra)]] *[[Parroquia (Ecuador)]] *[[Parroquia (Spain)]] *[[Parroquia (Venezuela)]]
